      "query": "I need the exact part number for a Schneider Modicon M241 PLC with 40 I/O and relay outputs, powered by 24V DC. We are standardizing this for our new assembly line and cannot accept the transistor output version.",
      "agent": {
        "text": "I cannot provide a specific SKU because Schneider Electric does not manufacture a Modicon M241 base controller that matches all of your requirements. \n\nBased on the Schneider Electric catalog, the output type on M241 PLCs dictates the required power supply:\n* **Relay output models** with 40 I/O (such as `TM241C40R` and the Ethernet-equipped `TM241CE40R`) are strictly built for **100\u2013240V AC** power supplies.\n* **24V DC powered models** with 40 I/O (such as `TM241C40T`, `TM241CE40T`, `TM241C40U`, and `TM241CE40U`) exclusively feature **transistor outputs**.\n\nBecause your new assembly line strictly requires 24V DC base power and cannot accept transistor outputs, a single all-in-one M241 SKU does not exist. \n\nTo stay within the Modicon M241 family, you will have to compromise by choosing one of the following workaround strategies:\n1. Change your design to provide 120/240V AC power to the PLC to use a relay model (`TM241C40R` or `TM241CE40R`).\n2. Order a 24V DC transistor model (`TM241C40T` or `TM241CE40T`) and wire the transistor outputs to external interposing relays. \n3. Order a 24V DC base controller and snap on Modicon TM3 relay expansion modules to hit your I/O requirements.",
