    {
      "query": "Provide the commercial reference number for a PowerPact H-frame circuit breaker, 100A, 3-pole, 600VAC, with a thermal-magnetic trip unit and EverLink lugs. It must have a 65k AIC rating at 480V for our main panel upgrade.",
      "agent": {
        "text": "The commercial reference number that matches your electrical specifications is **HJL36100** (Schneider Electric / Square D).\n\nThis part number provides the following:\n* **Frame:** PowerPact H-Frame\n* **Amperage:** 100A\n* **Poles:** 3-pole\n* **Voltage:** 600VAC\n* **Trip Unit:** Thermal-magnetic\n* **Interrupting Rating:** 65kA at 480V (designated by the \"J\" in the SKU)\n\n**Important Clarification on EverLink Lugs:**\nYou cannot order an H-frame breaker with EverLink lugs. EverLink creep-compensating terminals are an exclusive feature of the PowerPact **B-frame** series. The B-frame, however, is only rated for 600Y/347VAC maximum, whereas the H-frame is rated for true 600VAC (Delta). \n\nThe **HJL36100** comes standard with mechanical lugs (Part # AL150HD, accepting 14\u20133/0 AWG Al/Cu wire). \n\nIf you strictly require EverLink lugs and your main panel is 480V or 600Y/347V (not 600V Delta), the exact B-frame equivalent is **BJL36100**. If your system requires the full 600VAC rating, stick with the **HJL36100** and use the standard mechanical lugs.",
